ymentError(forStripeError:)","abstract":[{"text":"Converts Stripe errors into the appropriate Apple Pay error, for use in ","type":"text"},{"code":"PKPaymentAuthorizationResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If the error can be fixed by the customer within the Apple Pay sheet, we return an NSError that can be displayed in the Apple Pay sheet."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Otherwise, the original error is returned, resulting in the Apple Pay sheet being dismissed. You should display the error message to the customer afterwards."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Currently, we convert billing address related errors into a PKPaymentError that helpfully points to the billing address field in the Apple Pay sheet.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Note that Apple Pay should prevent most card errors (e.g. invalid CVC, expired cards) when you add a card to the wallet.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/stripeapplepay\/stripecore\/stpapiclient\/pkpaymenterror(forstripeerror:)","title":"pkPaymentError(forStripeError:)","role":"symbol"}}}